wall;
she
then
went
down
to
prayers.
When
she
returned
to
her
chamber,
it
was
to
meet
the
memory
of
Robert.
Slumber's
visitation
was
long
averted.
Long
she
sat
at
her
lattice,
long
gazed
down
on
the
old
garden
and
older
church,
on
the
tombs
laid
out
all
gray
and
calm,
and
clear
in
